        "created_at": "2024-12-03T04:11:24.155Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Signal currently supports taking a photo from the app, and sharing it so that it can be viewed only once. I.e. after that, the photo is not stored on neither the senderâ€™s nor the receiversâ€™ phones. However, we have to remember changing from viewing the picture infinitely to once every time before sending.</p>\n<p>Like we can configure messages to disappear after a given time for each conversation, it would be really nice to set a default so that all pictures shared in a conversation always disappears after being viewed once.</p>",
