        "created_at": "2024-12-04T23:51:26.575Z",
        "cooked": "<p>That existing request is not exactly what I am looking for. However, it was an interesting read.</p>\n<p>We have two different mechanisms for how photos disappear:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Timer - can be set on conversation-level, and applies to both text and other media</li>\n<li>Number-of-times-viewed - can be set per photo to 1 or infinity</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I would like to be able to set the limit for Number-of-times-viewed to photos on conversation-level. I do realize a workaround is to use a very short timer, but it is not the same.</p>\n<p>For photos, it would be nice to be able to choose between three alternatives, and which one to use as default should be configurable per conversation:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>View once (icon 1)</li>\n<li>View for a given time set in conversation (icon clock)</li>\n<li>View for infinity (icon infinity)</li>\n</ul>",
        "post_number": 3,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
        "updated_at": "2024-12-04T23:51:26.575Z",
